{
  "doc_id": "45260",
  "text": "VPREB3 (pre-B lymphocyte protein 3) is expressed in APAs and adjacent tissues, but not in cortisol-producing adenomas (see data in the online-only Data Supplement). [CITATION_1] In the normal cortex, it occurs mainly in the normal ZG, with only few positive cells in ZF. [CITATION_2] The colocalization of VPREB3 with CYP11B2 and the increased expression VPREB3 in H295R cells after angiotensin II stimulation suggest that VPREB3 could be a marker of aldosterone-producing cells. [CITATION_3] Nevertheless, the expression of VPREB3 in some ZF cells and the correlation between expression of VPREB3 and HSD3B2, but not HSD3B1, does not support VPREB3 as marker of ZG and APA cells.",
